Israeli Stocks: Ampal-American Israel, Hot Telecommunication

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-09-11T10:32:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-11/israeli-stocks-ampal-american-israel-hot-telecommunication.html
Israel’s TA-25 Index lost the most
since Sept. 6, declining 2.7 percent to 1,033.63 at 1:18 p.m. in
Tel Aviv.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Ampal-American Israel (AMPL)  Corp, which has a stake in
the company that supplies gas from  Egypt , plunged to the lowest
on record, falling 13 percent to 1.223 shekels. Egypt’s ruling
military council declared a state of emergency to restore order
after protesters attacked the Israeli embassy in Cairo.  Hot Telecommunication System Ltd. (HOT)   advanced the
most since Aug. 31, increasing as much as 3 percent to 47.47
shekels. The cable-service provider received changes to the
structure of the purchase for MIRS Communication Ltd., the
wireless operator, which lowers the value of the deal to 1.2
billion shekels ($323 million) from 1.3 billion shekels.
Separately, Hot said it received regulatory approval for the
merger.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in  Tel Aviv  at 
